 face of technological and scientific innovations? What culture-critical counter-schemes have been proposed?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCivilization, Moderny19th centuryvCongresses. 0aCivilization, Moderny20th centuryvCongresses. 0aLiterature, Moderny19th centuryxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aLiterature, Moderny20th centuryxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 4aDeutsch. 4aEnglisch. 4aProsa. 4aReise ‹Motiv›. 4aZeitreise. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh1 aBenesch, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGendolla, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriem, Julika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriem, Julika, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHubig, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKohl, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKörte, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichelucci, Stefania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPfeiffer, Κ. Ludwig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchenkel, Elmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeeber, Hans Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeeber, Hans Ulrich, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVoigts-Virchow, Eckart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeissen, Caecilie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz97834844